http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Software-engineer-murdered/article14010081.ece

A software engineer was found murdered at her apartment in Kadugodi on Tuesday night. Kusuma Rani, a native of Punjab and working in IBM, was staying alone in an apartment in Brindavan Layout. The murder came to light when one of her friends visited her apartment. The assailant had strangulated her to death. Police suspect that someone known to her might have killed her as there was no forced entry into the house. The police are investigating to ascertain whether any valuables were missing.